  "about": {
    "title": "CORNERSTONE Open Platform",
    "subtitle": "OPENSOURCE PDK live monitor",
    "version": "v1.0.0",
    "contact": "pdk.cornerstone.soton.ac.uk",
    "notes": "Licence free PDK monitoring and management dashboard for silicon photonics rapid prototyping.\nDesigned by Emre Kaplan (beta: 01/05/2026 · official v1.0.0 public release: 26/05/2026).\n\nFEATURES\n• Multi-platform tabs with per-platform BB libraries, GDS imports, S-matrix data, tests and fabrication files.\n• Role-based access: Admin (full), User-admin (own users/<id>/ folder), Read-only (view + run scripts).\n• Real-files architecture — every uploaded item lives as a separate file in the GitHub repo; the dashboard.json stays small and pool members hydrate the real bytes on fetch.\n• Multi-user pool assembly: 📥 Fetch all enabled sources, 📚 Fetch user repos (one-click pool), 🔍 Discover user slices, 🪪 Fetch my slice.\n• Full user-admin control over their users/<id>/ folder: add, remove (auto-prune orphans on publish), nuke (🗑 Wipe my repo folder).\n• Duplicate resolver for cross-platform BB names, with user-selectable keeper and variants.\n• GDS layers list with hover descriptions and colours.\n• Augmented BB procedural sketches with material gradients.\n• Inline Python script runner with safe sandbox.\n• Local Backups (.json) on every replace.\n\nThe portal is open to everyone for further development.\n\n",
    "logoUrl": "data:image/png;base64,",
